{
  "texts": [
    "In the medical domain, multimodal language models offer a promising direction for further research.",
    "In Figure 3, we present a partial display of the content from four multimodal datasets.",
    "DatasetsMedical visual question answering (Med-VQA) has tremendous potential in medicine, particularly in fields such as radiology and pathology.",
    "These two fields are rich in both imaging data and textual reports, making them prime candidates for VQA applications.VQA-RAD [76] is a manually-crafted dataset in radiology where questions and answers are given by clinicians.",
    "It contains 3,515 visual questions of 11 types and 315 corresponding radiological images.SLAKE [77] is a large bilingual dataset with comprehensive semantic labels annotated by experienced physicians and an extendable knowledge base for Med-VQA."
  ]
}